<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-05-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-05-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="1179" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1179">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">125.633/5–2649: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-05-26T13:00:00-04:00">May 26,
                                    1949—1 p. m.</date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>640. From Butterworth.<note n="60" xml:id="d1179fn60">W. Walton
                                Butterworth, Director of the Office of Far Eastern Affairs.</note>
                            We are all very disturbed by protracted confinement Ward and other
                            members staff Mukden and wish no stone left unturned to effect their
                            speedy departure. I hope you will find means personally to press this
                            matter to a rapid conclusion. [Butterworth.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Webb</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>